descriptionMarkdown:
So I decided to bring you everything you need to built your belt arrays. This will be a series of multiple Blueprints books I am going to post. Going: Yellow, Red, Blue, Yellow Addendum, Red Addendum and Blue Addendum.

Everything was named and categorized in such a way as to help to navigate and recognize the blueprints with just as single sight of them.

Balancers included:

--1 to: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

--...

--..up to..

--...

--8 to: 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

Further Extra's later on:

--Very Large or Unique Balancers: 12-to-12, 24-to24, 16-to-16, 32-to-32, Ytterby, Fractal Balancer's.

--Main-Bus Split-off belts and Priority Splitters made with either Circuit Conditions or using the mechanical logic of the Yellow, Red and Blue Splitters.

Credits should go, but are not limited, to the following REDDIT'ors and FORUM'ers:

RedditNamesAreShort - 12to12, 24to24 balancers, Yet Another Belt Balancer Compendium; MadZuri - 8to8, Universal8to8, Belt balancer compendium; Yttrium - Ytterby Balancer; QonQon - Fractal Balancers; ICantThinkOfABetterUsername - Imgur Belt Balancer Compendium; [deleted] - Count Perfect N to M Belt Balancers; ribsngibs - Further development of 8+ balancers and Fractal Balancer idea; Steejo and Arumba - Priority Spliter Makers/Testers; Lord_Peppe - Further refinement of the Priority Splitter; jhg300 - Priority splitter development;

EDIT1: Corrected the 4:5 balancer.
